## Docker Deployment

```bash
# Build the Docker image
npm run docker:build

# Start with Docker Compose (includes health check, restart policy, log rotation)
npm run docker:up

# View logs
npm run docker:logs

# Stop services
npm run docker:down
```

The generated `Dockerfile` uses multi-stage builds for small production images.
The `docker-compose.yml` includes health checks, log rotation (10MB/3 files), and auto-restart.

### Environment Variables

Copy `.env.example` to `.env` and configure:

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

Required variables:
- `{{#if (eq config.llm "openai")}}OPENAI_API_KEY{{else}}{{#if (eq config.llm "anthropic")}}ANTHROPIC_API_KEY{{else}}{{#if (eq config.llm "deepseek")}}DEEPSEEK_API_KEY{{else}}# No API key required for mock provider{{/if}}{{/if}}{{/if}}` — Your LLM provider API key
- `PORT` — Server port (default: 3000)

